HEADWORD: Howadji
<hw>How*adj"i</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ar.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A traveler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A merchant; -- so called in the East because
merchants were formerly the chief travelers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Howbeit</ent>⟦br⟧
